    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Mentions",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 47,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/character/Albedo_icon.png",
                      "menu_id": 2,
                      "name": "Albedo",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 2",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "\"Albedo got into Mondstadt because of his master's recommendation letter.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "This statement is technically true. But Monstadt's gates are open to everyone, and he would have been quite welcome even without the recommendation letter.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In fact, Albedo's life in Mondstadt may even have been more comfortable without it.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "This is because the recipient of the letter was the famed travel writer, Alice, an old friend of Albedo's master, Rhinedottir.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "After receiving the letter, Alice considered its requests.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"So, Rhine said that you'll need a laboratory... And not one of a size that a civilian could build, either. Hmm... I know!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "And just like that, she threw him into the Knights of Favonius.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The work of the Knights was actually quite easy for Albedo, requiring only five percent of his energy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The rest of his energy could be spent on experiments, with the Knights' full range of apparatus at his disposal, he thought.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "And yet...",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Alice has a daughter, named Klee.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Yes, \"that\" Klee.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"We'll be a family from now on, treat her like a real younger sister!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "From that day forth, cleaning up after Klee would come to take up most of Albedo's remaining energy...",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 3",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Albedo has no memory of any blood relations. From as far back as he can remember, he was already adventuring deep within domains with his master.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Of course, Miss Alice, the Knights of Favonius, and that traveler who had a sense of the stellar depths about them... They are all important people. And yet his master is unquestionably the most special to him.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "For Albedo, she is his only kin.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She was a cold and strict woman who raised him and taught him the secrets of alchemy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"The universe is the sable essence of the true starry sky... Earth is the accumulated memory of time and being...",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Chalk: that is you. Soil is where alchemy derives its name, and is the basis of all life. And this...\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She demonstrated her technique before him as a huge life form burst from its culture tank in a shower of shattered fragments.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"...This is new birth.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 4",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Albedo once led a simple and content existence.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "There was no need for him to contemplate anything. Life was uneventful, its meaning consisted of nothing more than accompanying his teacher, doing what she asked of him, and meeting her expectations.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "But one day, deep in the heart of a dungeon, master and apprentice discovered an artifact known as The Heart of Naberius.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "And with that, his master disappeared, leaving naught but a note, a recommendation letter, and a classical text behind.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Upon the note was written: \"Albedo, go to Mondstadt. Find my old friend, Alice, and give her the recommendation letter. Then, complete your final assignment.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The classical text was one of the last extant manuscripts of the Opus Magnum from his master's collection.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "If one were to push the definition a little, she had left him another gift — the title of Kreideprinz, and with it, a written acknowledgment that she had nothing further to teach him.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In the past, Albedo's assignments had always been very difficult.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "He had always believed wholeheartedly that his master would make good on her threat to leave him, should he fail.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "But this assignment she had left to him was far too hard, far beyond the limit of his abilities.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Did this mean, then, that he was fated to never complete it, and thus never see his master again?",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"Your final assignment: show me the truth and the meaning of this world.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 5",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The alchemy that Albedo commands is wholly different from any of the arts practiced in the Seven Nations of Teyvat.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Its lineage can be traced back to the nation of Khaenri'ah.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Khaenri'ah was an underground realm, with precious few natural fauna. As such, its alchemy focused more heavily on the creation of life.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "This art of creation was known as \"The Art of Khemia.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Albedo had learned of this in his youth from reading his master's notes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The next stage after \"soil\" is \"chalk,\" which was also something his master had mentioned.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"Chalk is the spotless soil, and was used to make primordial man.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Now, Albedo understands alchemy in far greater depth than he did in the beginning, and his knowledge on the subject is far more comprehensive.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"From soil was birthed chalk.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The profundity of this statement is well understood by Albedo now.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Such ineffable secrets are bound up with his fond memories of his master.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She was not his birth mother, but there is no doubt that his life stems from her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"I hope this isn't just wishful thinking, but... when parents speak to their children about 'the meaning of this world'... surely they just mean the pursuit of a happy life?\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "From time to time, Albedo finds himself musing on this sentiment.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Voice-Overs",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "About Family",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Family? Although Alice has always asked me to call her \"Mother,\" when I think of the idea of \"family,\" my master comes to mind first. My earliest memories in life are of going on adventures with her. She taught me the art of alchemy and much knowledge about the world. Perhaps... even the words \"family\" and \"master\" are incapable of fully expressing her meaning to me.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "More About Albedo: V",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Even now, I find the nigredo processing stage of alchemy passed down by my master to be full of mystery. What did my master want to create using this technique...? My research is far from over. I will require your help to investigate further.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "When It Snows",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Master...",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:#ffffff"
                      ],
                      "text": "Dialogues",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:#ffd780"
                      ],
                      "text": "About Durin",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "This dragon's life force resonates with me...",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Not because it's a dragon, but because I am... me.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Rhinedottir... Master... Is this your creation, the giant dragon Durin?",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Was the two of us meeting really a good thing?",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 6367,
                      "icon_url": "",
                      "name": "Alice",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Dialogues",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "About the Hexenzirkel",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "\"A flower that is not of this world\" signifies, of course, flowers that do not naturally exist in this world. This is the signature of R, full name Rhinedottir, also known as \"Gold.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "If there's anyone in this world who could create a flower species that does not yet exist, it would be her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4914,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/04/237301566/fa4c986eefe97522566b35be6e29e7a0_8375787056238346663.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Elynas",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:#ffffff"
                      ],
                      "text": "Dialogues",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:#ffd780"
                      ],
                      "text": "About Mother",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "My mother is the reason I exist. Mother is the most wonderful person in this world. She gave me my name — and it is a lovely name.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Before I was born, I floated in the cosmic darkness. It was cold there, and lonely. I was so sad, then, and I would often cry.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "But later, I heard Mother's voice.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "She wished for me to be born into a beautiful world, to give me life, to give me a strong and healthy body that could walk the world, to grant me a beautiful name.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "She wanted to give me many siblings, wanted me to meet many friends, wanted me to see the beautiful sights beyond that cosmic dark.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "She did not deceive me, and I was very happy. My elder siblings treated me well, and later, many younger ones came along — and I treated them just as my elder siblings treated me.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Later, we left the world beneath the earth. I felt the wind brushing against my skin, the warmth of the sun, waters icy and warm.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Life is wonderful — and it was wonderful that I was able to witness this world!",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Only later did I discover that I was different from the life in this world. The things that brought me happiness, the things that interested me... they were frightening and terribly hurtful to those of this world.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Eventually, I fell here and died. That saddened yet gladdened me. I treasured the life I was given by Mother, but my life would bring everyone such pain... so it was better this way.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Later, just as Mother gave me life, I gave my children life, that they may walk upon this world — that makes me very proud and very happy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
